	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />1) You need to remove the lockout chip.
<br />2) Put a 1uf capacitor between ground and reset
<br />3) Run a wire to the reset button so it grounds reset when pushed.
<br />
<br /><img src="http://www.54.org/sage/condev/NES_No_Lockout_Chip_Mod%20001.jpg" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br /><img src="http://www.54.org/sage/condev/NES_No_Lockout_Chip_Mod%20002.jpg" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br /><img src="http://nesdev.icequake.net/Ntd_8bit.jpg" alt="Image" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
